this snippet presents a way to create macros in F# to automato VS IDE environment.

To compile, just open a Command prompt window and type:
      fsc --out:fsmacros.dll --reference:envdte.dll --target:library fsmacros.fs

Where FSMACROS.FS is the file name I gave for the code. 
After compile, copy the dll to 
    C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio 10.0\Common7\IDE\PublicAssemblies

To use, just open F# interactive in Visual Studio (CTRL+ALT+F) and type:
   #r “envdte”;;
   #r “fsmacros”;;
   Let dte = vs10macros.getDte “The main window title appearing in you VS 2010”;;

